Execution Steps: Jenkins Pipeline (From Scratch)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Open Jenkins ‚Üí New Item

Click New Item

Enter name: student-crud-pipeline

Select Pipeline

Click OK

2Ô∏è‚É£ Configure GitHub Source

Scroll to Pipeline ‚Üí Definition

Select Pipeline script from SCM

SCM: Git

Repository URL:

https://github.com/<your-username>/<repo>.git


Credentials: Add if repo is private

Branch: main

3Ô∏è‚É£ Jenkinsfile inside your GitHub repo

Create a file named Jenkinsfile at the root of your project:

pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {

        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main',
                    url: 'https://github.com/<your-username>/<repo>.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean install'
            }
        }

        stage('Run Tests') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn test'
            }
        }

    }

    post {
        success {
            echo "BUILD SUCCESSFUL!"
        }
        failure {
            echo "BUILD FAILED!"
        }
    }
}


üí° On Windows Jenkins use bat instead of sh:

bat 'mvn clean install'
bat 'mvn test'


Commit and push:

git add Jenkinsfile
git commit -m "Added Jenkinsfile"
git push

4Ô∏è‚É£ Run the Pipeline

In Jenkins:

Open your pipeline ‚Üí Click Build Now

5Ô∏è‚É£ View Build Results

Jenkins ‚Üí select the build number (#1, #2, etc.)

Click Console Output

You will see:

[INFO] BUILD SUCCESS
Tests run: 5, Failures: 0, Errors: 0


If a test fails:

[ERROR] BUILD FAILURE
